  "response": "The icons commonly used for play, pause, record, rewind, and stop were designed by John H. Eargle and Ronald M. Burk. They developed these symbols in the late 1960s while working for the industrial design firm, Bell & Howell. The symbols were originally designed for use on tape recorders and later became standardized across various audio and video equipment.",
